      "citation_id": "[CITATION_1]",
      "span_text": "The winter hardiness of meadow fescue (F. pratensis) is sufficient for Latvian conditions [CITATION_1] , and is superior to that of perennial ryegrass (L. perenne) and Lolium type Festulolium accessions, however persistence is comparatively low, and is not significantly different from perennial ryegrass and Festulolium accessions."
